column5: Finally got enough ice to move my shack out to deeper water and made this video of the move   <iframe width="420" height="315" src="" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
I think your missing the attachment?
Nice setup Mikeyfish, sure works well.
That's quite the setup you have mikey!Also like those tracks on your vehicle.
glad someone has found some safe ice
Sweet set up for sure! I'm interested in those tracks. Did you fab those yourself? How cool would my forester XT be with tracks on it....yeehaw!  S.
Yes I made the adaption hubs myself. A machine shop would charge about $1500 to make
Dang!  Now that's what I call an ice fishing setup!
Thats over and above the price of the actual tracks, right?  If someone could make me the whole set up for that price, I think I'd order them tomorrow

I had the tracks off my quad and the adapters I built on my chums lathe for less than $100.00, and took them to a local machine shop to get a price for them to build $1500. They said they wouldn't change a thing and would build them the same and they took measurements.
